dcterms:description: FashionMNIST is a dataset consisting of 60,000 grayscale images of clothing items, each with a resolution of 28x28 pixels. It is used to benchmark machine learning algorithms and explore color shift magnitude as a function of image size.
dcterms:title: FashionMNIST

dcterms:creator: Tobias Bischoff
Katherine Deck
dcterms:description: This dataset consists of snapshots from a two-dimensional fluid flow simulation, specifically focusing on the moisture supersaturation field, which is used to compute precipitation. The dataset includes 800 samples of 512x512 images with multiple channels corresponding to different dynamical state variables.
dcterms:title: Two-dimensional fluid flow simulation (moisture supersaturation field)
